item.title: Oil Tumbles on Dollar Strength, Economy Worries
item.description: Oil prices slipped, with Brent on course for its sixth consecutive loss, as a strong dollar and concerns about the global economy weighed on prices.

item.title: Rising US Bond Yields Lift Dollar to Multi-Month Highs
item.description: Rising Treasury yields have lifted the dollar to a 10-month high against a basket of currencies and a six-month high against the euro, with ING saying “technical analysts will be dusting off calls for a move to the 107.20 area” for the DXY dollar index.

item.title: Metals Slip As Industrial Demand Remains Weak
item.description: Base metals and gold prices fell in early London trading, as weak demand in China, and an uncertain macroeconomic environment pressured industrial goods.

item.title: Eurozone Bond Yields Rise as Markets Adjust to High-For-Long Policy Rates
item.description: Eurozone government bond yields rose as markets continued to come to terms with central banks’ intention to keep interest rates high for long, Natixis said.

item.title: Canada Speaker Apologizes for Honoring Alleged Nazi Soldier
item.description: The speaker of Canada’s legislature issued an apology on Monday, after he honored a man identified by Jewish advocacy groups as a former officer of a Nazi military unit that fought against the Russians.

item.title: Nikkei Falls 1.1%, Dragged by Pharma, Electronics Stocks
item.description: Japanese stocks ended lower, dragged by declines in pharmaceutical and electronics stocks, as concerns persisted about policy tightening abroad and higher borrowing costs.

item.title: Ford Tried to Sell the Electric Mustang to China the Tesla Way---It Didn't Work
item.description: The Detroit automaker is changing its strategy after China EV sales suffered from marketing and sales missteps.

item.title: The World Needs New Antibiotics, but the Business Model Is Broken
item.description: New drugs to defeat “superbug” bacteria aren’t reaching patients.

item.title: As Its U.S. Shop Opens, TikTok'sChinese Merchants Struggle to Sell Mops, Soap Dispensers
item.description: Picking the right product, avoiding cultural faux pas and navigating social media are all part of challenges even experienced exporters face.

item.title: U.S. Abrams Tanks Reach Ukraine. Is It a Case of Too Little, Too Late?
item.description: The Abrams are among the world’s most sophisticated tanks and offer technical advantages that older tanks can’t match.

item.title: Americans Finally Start to Feel the Sting From the Fed's Rate Hikes
item.description: For families who don’t need to borrow, higher rates might not affect daily life. But for those who do, higher rates are really starting to hurt.

item.title: Intel's Big Chip-Making Push in Germany Hits Bottleneck
item.description: A worker shortage and high energy prices in the country pose challenges for the U.S. company’s planned semiconductor factory.

item.title: How GOP Infighting With McCarthy Could Lead to a Government Shutdown
item.description: House Speaker Kevin McCarthy is facing opposition from within the Republican Party over a short-term spending bill. WSJ’s Tim Hanrahan breaks down how this power struggle could lead to a government shutdown.
